---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="BeaconGuard Assurance | Runtime Control and Evidence Boundary"
  description="BeaconGuard is a deterministic control and evidence boundary for high-risk enterprise workflows across healthcare, financial services, and regulated internal automation. It returns explicit ALLOW or DENY results before governed execution."
>
  <section class="landing">
    <p class="hero-eyebrow">BeaconGuard Runtime Control Boundary</p>
    <h1>Policy control before governed execution. Evidence after every decision.</h1>
    <p class="hero-subheadline">
      BeaconGuard is a deterministic control and evidence boundary for high-risk enterprise workflows across healthcare, financial services, and regulated internal automation.
    </p>
    <p class="hero-subheadline">
      BeaconGuard evaluates trusted request context against the Active Verified Release and returns an explicit ALLOW or DENY result before governed execution. Every deterministic result produces a Verifiable Decision Record.
    </p>
    <div class="page-actions">
      <a class="btn-primary" href="/platform">Review the Platform</a>
      <a class="btn-secondary" href="/healthcare">Healthcare Architecture Review</a>
      <a class="btn-secondary" href="/fintech">Financial Workflow Review</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section
    class="stack-section homepage-block product-overview-section"
    aria-labelledby="product-overview-title"
  >
    <div class="product-overview-heading">
      <p class="section-label">Product Overview</p>
      <h2 id="product-overview-title">
        Runtime assurance for AI in regulated industries
      </h2>
      <p>
        BeaconGuard introduces a deterministic control and evidence boundary between enterprise workflows and governed AI, APIs, or automated systems. This overview explains the business risk, the operating model, and the value of enforcing approved controls before governed execution.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="product-overview-video">
      <iframe
        src="https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/OzPMIQ_NHho"
        title="BeaconGuard product overview: Runtime assurance for AI in regulated industries"
        loading="lazy"
        allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share"
        referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin"
        allowfullscreen
      ></iframe>
    </div>

    <p class="product-overview-qualifier">
      This overview explains BeaconGuard’s purpose and operating model. It is not a live product demonstration.
    </p>

    <div class="product-overview-validation">
      <h3>Continue with technical validation</h3>
      <div class="page-actions product-overview-actions">
        <a class="btn-primary" href="/docs/architecture">Review System Architecture</a>
        <a class="product-overview-link" href="/how-it-works">See How It Works</a>
        <a class="product-overview-link" href="/security">Review Security and Trust</a>
        <a class="product-overview-link" href="/design-partner-program">Request a Controlled Evaluation</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="stack-section homepage-block">
    <h2>Business outcomes</h2>
    <p>
      BeaconGuard keeps existing enterprise applications in place while inserting a fail-closed control boundary before governed AI, APIs, or automated systems execute.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Existing applications continue to own workflow logic and systems of record.</li>
      <li>Deterministic ALLOW or DENY results are returned before governed execution.</li>
      <li>Verifiable Decision Records support security, privacy, compliance, risk, and audit review without changing the enforcement result.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="stack-section homepage-block">
    <h2>Control boundary at a glance</h2>
    <p>
      Compliance Playbooks are validated, compiled, approved, signed, and distributed through the BeaconGuard Control Plane. Only an Active Verified Release governs runtime evaluation. The BeaconGuard Runtime Control Boundary validates request context, performs trust, freshness, and replay checks, evaluates the request deterministically, and returns ALLOW or DENY before downstream execution.
    </p>
    <p>
      When required approvals or trust conditions are absent, BeaconGuard returns DENY with an explicit deterministic reason. An illustrative reason style is <code>APPROVAL_REQUIRED</code>. Human or governance review may follow from the Verifiable Decision Record; review does not permit execution.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="stack-section homepage-block">
    <h2>Industry review paths</h2>
    <div class="section-grid section-grid--compact">
      <div class="content-card">
        <h3>Healthcare Operations</h3>
        <p>For PHI-sensitive operational workflows, approved pathways, role-based request controls, and Verifiable Decision Records for privacy and compliance review.</p>
        <p><a href="/healthcare">Review Healthcare Use Case</a></p>
      </div>
      <div class="content-card">
        <h3>Financial Workflows</h3>
        <p>For AML, KYC, fraud, dispute review, and customer-impacting recommendations that require deterministic request control before governed execution.</p>
        <p><a href="/fintech">Review Financial Use Case</a></p>
      </div>
      <div class="content-card">
        <h3>Regulated Internal Automation</h3>
        <p>For internal agents or automations that need fail-closed enforcement before acting against production systems or sensitive operational data.</p>
        <p><a href="/canonical-workflow">Review Workflow Examples</a></p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="stack-section homepage-block">
    <h2>Technical validation</h2>
    <p>
      Continue from the business case into the architecture, runtime sequence, security posture, and evidence surfaces reviewers use during due diligence.
    </p>
    <div class="page-actions">
      <a class="btn-primary" href="/docs/architecture">System Architecture</a>
      <a class="btn-secondary" href="/how-it-works">How It Works</a>
      <a class="btn-secondary" href="/proof-evidence">Proof and Evidence</a>
      <a class="btn-secondary" href="/trust-assurance">Trust Center</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="stack-section homepage-block">
    <h2>Request a Controlled Evaluation</h2>
    <p>
      Use a bounded workflow review to validate boundary placement, Compliance Playbook mapping, ALLOW and DENY cases, evidence review, and deployment fit without replacing existing systems of record.
    </p>
    <div class="page-actions">
      <a class="btn-primary" href="/design-partner-program">Start Controlled Evaluation</a>
      <a class="btn-secondary" href="/contact">Contact architecture@beaconguardassurance.com</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <style>
    .home-boundary-section,
    .homepage-block {
      overflow-wrap: anywhere;
      word-break: break-word;
    }

    .product-overview-section {
      margin: -0.75rem auto 3.5rem;
    }

    .product-overview-heading {
      max-width: 780px;
      margin: 0 auto 1.5rem;
      text-align: center;
    }

    .product-overview-heading .section-label {
      text-align: center;
    }

    .product-overview-heading h2 {
      margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    }

    .product-overview-heading p {
      max-width: 720px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      color: var(--text-secondary);
    }

    .product-overview-video {
      width: min(880px, 100%);
      margin: 0 auto;
      aspect-ratio: 16 / 9;
      overflow: hidden;
      border: 1px solid rgba(148, 163, 184, 0.28);
      border-radius: 0.6rem;
      background: #0b1220;
    }

    .product-overview-video iframe {
      display: block;
      width: 100%;
      height: 100%;
      border: 0;
    }

    .product-overview-qualifier {
      max-width: 720px;
      margin: 0.75rem auto 0;
      text-align: center;
      font-size: 0.82rem;
      font-weight: 400;
      line-height: 1.45;
      color: var(--text-muted);
    }

    .product-overview-validation {
      max-width: 880px;
      margin: 1.25rem auto 0;
      text-align: center;
    }

    .product-overview-validation h3 {
      margin: 0 0 0.7rem;
      font-size: 0.98rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      color: var(--text-primary);
    }

    .product-overview-actions {
      justify-content: center;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 0.65rem 1.15rem;
    }

    .product-overview-link {
      display: inline-block;
      padding: 0.45rem 0.15rem;
      color: var(--text-secondary);
      font-size: 0.92rem;
      font-weight: 500;
      text-decoration: underline;
      text-underline-offset: 0.18em;
      text-decoration-thickness: 1px;
      border: 0;
      background: transparent;
    }

    .product-overview-link:hover,
    .product-overview-link:focus-visible {
      color: var(--text-primary);
    }

    @media (max-width: 900px) {
      .product-overview-heading,
      .product-overview-qualifier,
      .product-overview-validation {
        text-align: left;
      }

      .product-overview-heading .section-label {
        text-align: left;
      }

      .product-overview-actions {
        justify-content: flex-start;
      }
    }
  </style>
</BaseLayout>
